---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const title = "Disclaimer | UPI QR";
const description = "Regulatory and legal disclaimer for UPI QR. We are an independent tool and have no official affiliation with NPCI.";
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <main class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 py-12 md:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="rounded-[2rem] border border-white/70 bg-white/85 p-6 shadow-md md:p-10">
      <a href="/" class="text-sm font-bold text-leaf hover:underline">&larr; Back to Generator</a>
      
      <h1 class="mt-6 text-4xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-forest md:text-5xl">Legal Disclaimer</h1>
      <p class="mt-2 text-xs text-forest/50">Last Updated: June 8, 2026</p>

      <div class="mt-8 space-y-6 text-sm leading-relaxed text-forest/80">
        <section class="space-y-3">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-forest">1. No Affiliation with NPCI / BHIM / UPI</h2>
          <p>
            UPI QR is an independent web utility and is <strong>not associated, affiliated, authorized, endorsed by, or in any official capacity connected with</strong> the National Payments Corporation of India (NPCI), BHIM, Unified Payments Interface (UPI) network, or any governmental regulatory bodies. 
          </p>
          <p>
            The official website of NPCI can be accessed at <a href="https://www.npci.org.in" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-leaf underline font-semibold">npci.org.in</a>. All official terms, policies, and API specifications relating to Unified Payments Interface are governed by NPCI.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="space-y-3">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-forest">2. Trademark Disclaimer</h2>
          <p>
            All product names, brand logos, and registered trademarks displayed on this site—including but not limited to <strong>Paytm, PhonePe, Google Pay, GPay, BHIM, and NPCI</strong>—are the exclusive property of their respective owners. 
          </p>
          <p>
            The inclusion of brand-styled template options, brand presets, or brand logos is done solely for consumer convenience (e.g., helping merchants indicate which scanner apps their QR code accommodates). Use of these trademarks does not imply any endorsement, sponsorship, or association between the trademark holders and UPI QR.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="space-y-3">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-forest">3. No Financial Services Offered</h2>
          <p>
            UPI QR <strong>does not process transactions, hold funds, intermediate payments, or offer banking or financial services</strong>. We provide a static text compilation tool. The QR codes generated by our application simply package the user's plain-text input parameters into a standard URI schema (`upi://pay?...`) defined by NPCI. All actual financial transactions occur on-device within the user's banking app through the standard UPI channel.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="space-y-3">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-forest">4. Use at Your Own Risk</h2>
          <p>
            We provide this tool for free to help small business owners and content creators. We offer no guarantees that the QR codes generated will operate uninterrupted, scan correctly on every device, or process without failure. Users must verify the generated QR code by performing a test scan before printing or placing it at payment checkout counters. We accept no liability for any errors, transaction failures, or lost revenue.
          </p>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
